      "id": "bug-014",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-24",
      "error_message": "Run sometimes sends cards back to deck face-up and interactive; next room may not deal all 4 cards",
      "file": "scripts/ScoundrelGame.cs (SyncRoomToGodot)",
      "root_cause": "draggable_object.gd card.move() early-returns when global_position == target_destination. After OnRunPressed() moves old room cards to the deck, their tweens start but _process hasn't run yet — the cards still sit at their old room-slot positions. If SyncRoomToGodot() then re-deals one of those cards back to the same room slot, card.move(room_slot_pos) sees global_position == room_slot_pos and early-returns, leaving the deck-bound tween running. That tween carries the card (now logically in the room, face-up and interactive) to the deck position.",
      "fix": "In SyncRoomToGodot(), set each new room card's global_position to _deckPile.global_position before calling move_cards on the room container. This ensures global_position != room_slot_pos, so card.move() always starts a fresh tween and kills the stale deck tween.",
      "tags": [
        "run",
        "deck",
        "card-state",
        "deal",
        "face-up",
        "interactive",
        "tween",
        "move-early-return"
      ],
      "related_bugs": [],
      "occurrences": 1,
      "last_seen": "2026-06-24"
    },
